    "The parameter σ LSST is the expected photometric error of LSST, and it can be approximated using",
    "where σ sys is the systematic photometric error and σ rand is the random photometric error.",
    "LSST aims to achieve a σ sys < 0.005 mag (Ivezić et al. 2019); we set σ sys to 0.005 mag in our simulation.",
    "The random photometric error (σ rand) is expected to scale as σ 2 rand = (0.04γ)x + γx 2 (mag 2), x = 10 0.4(m-m5), (8) where m 5 is the 5σ limiting magnitude in a given band (for point sources), and γ is a band-dependent factor (Ivezić et al. 2019).",
    "Following Ivezić et al. (2019), we set γ to 0.038 for u-band and to 0.039 for other LSST bands."
  ],
